						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the wall of the Sōmēśvarsvāmi temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 155[8], Yuva, Māgha, ba. 14, Monday.</p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Seems to register a grant made to the temple of Sōmēśvara at Kānūr by Pinamallu-Bhaṭṭa, son of Pōtukūchi Nāgam-Bhaṭṭa.</p>						

